lar trains from the country's main states. Taxis and cabs are available at all of these train stops. By Bus: Punjab has an extensive road network connecting the country's main cities and regions. National Highway 1, known as the Grand Trunk Road, connects it to most of North and East India. Buses also run between Punjab and neighbouring cities such as Delhi, Haryana, and Rajasthan. To explore the tourist attractions in Punjab, you can take a cab or taxi. Local Food of Punjab If planning a vacation to Punjab, you should know that your trip will be incomplete without experiencing the regional dishes. Every day here marks a unique celebration, energy, and cultural richness, a significant part of which is delicious and unique food. Colours, spices, and the most elaborate and diverse cooking methods abound here. Punjabi food includes parathas, tandoori chicken, naan, pakoras, and tasty paneer dishes. There are vegetarian and non-vegetarian dining alternatives available. Dishes are cooked with 'ghee' or butter to enhance the flavour of Punjabi cuisine. Aside from that, the food's powerful spices leave strong and exquisite flavours in your mouth here. The Punjabi cuisine include Butter Chicken, Tandoori Chicken, Shahi Paneer, Chole Bhature, Makki Di Roti, Sarson Da Saag, Dal Fry, Rajma Chawal, Punjabi Kadhi, Amritsari Fish, Aloo Gobhi, and Lassi. Aside from that, sweet foods like Gajar Ka Halwa, Jalebi, Kulfi, Rabri, Gulab Jamun, Barfi, Motichoor Laddu, and some traditional sweets. Best Time to Visit Punjab If you are considering a trip to Punjab and are wondering when is the ideal time to go, the best time to go is between October and March. The weather is good at the starting of the winter, but temperatures drop dramatically throughout the peak season. During the winter, you may visit the state without dealing with the oppressive heat or rain. Visiting tourist attractions around this time is a pleasurable experience. Visiting the state during summer is not suggested sinc